==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catcall
<hw>Cat"call`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A sound like the cry
of a cat, such as is made in playhouses to express dissatisfaction with
a play; also, a small shrill instrument for making such a
noise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Upon the rising of the curtain. I was very much surprised with the
great consort of <qex>catcalls</qex> which was exhibited.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catch</ent>⟦br⟧
